Road Accidents Analytics Dashboard - Power BI

ğŸ“Œ Overview

This Power BI dashboard provides an in-depth analysis of road accident trends and casualties, enabling data-driven decision-making for improved road safety. It visualizes key metrics such as total accidents, casualty trends, accident severity, location-based insights, and year-over-year (YoY) comparisons.

ğŸ“Š Key Features

Total Casualties & Accidents: Yearly trends with YoY comparisons.

Casualties by Accident Severity: Breakdown of minor, serious, and fatal accidents.

Monthly Trend Analysis: Casualty trends across months to identify seasonal patterns.

Casualties by Area & Time: Segmentation by location and time of the day (day/night).

Accidents by Road Type: Analysis of accident distribution across different road types.

Location-Based Analysis: Accident and casualty distribution by specific locations.

ğŸ“‚ Dataset

Contains ~300,000 records with various columns such as accident severity, location, date/time, road type, and casualty count.

Cleaned, transformed, and modeled for optimized Power BI performance.

ğŸ“ˆ Dashboard Insights & Improvements

Enhanced Data Visualization: Interactive visuals, heatmaps, and comparative charts.

Year-over-Year Comparison: Quick assessment of accident trends.

User-Friendly Interface: Filters, slicers, and drill-through reports for deeper analysis.

Better Decision-Making: Identifies high-risk areas and peak accident times for safety interventions.

